claims:
Claims 1. A system provided by an inventory management service provider to manage respective inventories of merchants, the system comprising: a set of instructions stored on a server associated with the service provider, the set of instructions to: maintain a database of inventory of a merchant, the database including data entries respectively corresponding to items offered for sale by the merchant, each data entry corresponding to an item type and a number indicating a quantity of items associated with the item type the merchant lias available for sale; and receive, from a merchant point-of-sale application stored on a merchant device operated by the merchant, instructions for updating the database; an inventory management application executable on a user device operated by a user, the user device being personal to the user, and the inventory management application comprising instructions to: receive, from the merchant device, temporary access provisioning of a functionality associated with the inventory management application, the temporary access provisioning grants the user device access to a sendee functionality for collecting inventory data while the user device is located in a particular region of a physical store of the merchant; receive, from a camera associated with the user device, image data associated with at least one item identifier corresponding to at least one item in the particular region; determine, based at least in part on the image data, inventory data associated with the particular region, the inventory data identifying a number of items and at. _ . least one associated item type that are in the particular region; aggregate the inventory data into a data package; and send the data package to the merchant point-of-sale application; and the merchant point-of-sale application stored on the merchant device operated by the merchant, the merchant point-of-sale application comprising instructions to: provision the temporary access to the service functionality to the inventory management application of the user device; receive, from the user device, tlie data package comprising the inventory data collected by the user device and associated with the particular region; 

 aggregate the inventory data with additional inventory data received from at least one other user device to generate aggregated inventory data, the additional inventory data associated with at least one other region of the physical store; receive an indication that the merchant approves the aggregated inventory data; and send the aggregated inventory data to the server with the instructions for updating the database, the server utilizing the aggregated inventory data to update the database. 2. A system as claim 1 recites, wherein: the inventory management application is stored on the user device; and providing the temporary access provisioning to the service functionality comprises providing a password, a code, or a key to the inventory management application to enable the temporary access provisioning to the service functionality. 3. A system as claim 1 recites, the merchant point-of-sale application further comprising instructions to initiate a download of the inventory management application onto the user device to provide the temporary access provisioning to the service functionality. 4. A system as claim 1 recites, wherein the inventory management application is accessible by the user device via a web interface. 5. A system as claim 1 recites, wherein the set of instructions stored on the server further compare the aggregated inventory data with previously determined aggregated inventory data; determine a similarity' value representing a similarity between the aggregated inventory data and the previously determined aggregated inventory data; determine that the similarity value is less than a threshold value; and send, to the entity application, instructions for presenting an indication to repeat inventory data collection. 6. A computer-implemented method for inventory management comprising: determining a characteristic associated with a user operating a device having an inventory management application; provisioning, based at least in part on the characteristic, temporary access to a service functionality associated with the inventory management application to the device, wherein the temporary access enables the device to collect item information associated with items available for acquisition from an entity; receiving, from the device, data associated with a first region of a physical store of the entity, the data identifying a number of items and at least one associated item type in the first region; aggregating the data with additional data received from at least one other device operated by at least one other user to generate aggregated data; .and sending the aggregated data to a service provider with the instructions for updating a database associated with items available for acquisition from the entity. 7. The computer-implemented method of claim 6, wherein the additional data is associated with the first region of the physical store or a second region of the physical store that is different than the first region. 8. The computer-implemented method of claim 6, further comprising: determining, based at least in part on location data associated with the device, that the device is outside of the first region; and terminating the provisioning of the temporary access to the service functionality. 9. The computer-implemented method of claim 6, further comprising: determining an expiration of a time interval associated with the provisioning of the temporary access to the service functionality; and terminating the provisioning of the temporary access to the service functionality. 10. The computer-implemented method of claim 6, further comprising presenting a graphical user interface that graphically represents the aggregated data 

 and provides functionality for the entity to at least one of modify or supplement the aggregated data prior to sending the aggregated data to the service provider. 11. An entity device operated by an entity, the entity device comprising: a display: one or more processors; one or more non-transitory computer-readable media storing instructions executable by the one or more processors, wherein the instructions program the one or more processors to perform actions comprising: provisioning temporary access to a functionality associated with a service that benefits the entity to a personal device of a user, the personal device having an inventory management application: detennining an occurrence of an event; and based at least in part on the occurrence of the event, terminating the provisioning of the temporary access to the functionality. 12. The entity device as claim 11 recites, the actions further comprising: presenting, via the display, a user interface identifying one or more personal devices respectively corresponding to one or more users that are available for provisioning of temporary access to the functionality; receiving an input corresponding to a selection of the personal device from the one or more personal devices to provide the provisioning of the temporary access to the functionality; and provisioning the temporary access to the functionality based at least in part on the input. 13. The entity device as claim 11 recites, wherein the event is an expiration of a period of time associated with the provisioning of the temporary access or a determination that the personal device is outside of a geo-fenced area associated with the provisioning of the temporary access.
